    <a href="#lists">Lists</a>
    <a href="#links">Links & Images</a>
  </nav>

  <section id="headings">
    <h2>HTML Headings</h2>
    <p>HTML provides six levels of headings, from <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> to <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code>.</p>
    <div class="example-box">
      <h1>FIRST REPOSITORY (h1)</h1>
      <h2>FIRST REPOSITORY (h2)</h2>
      <h3>FIRST REPOSITORY (h3)</h3>
      <h4>FIRST REPOSITORY (h4)</h4>
      <h5>FIRST REPOSITORY (h5)</h5>
      <h6>FIRST REPOSITORY (h6)</h6>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="paragraphs">
    <h2>Paragraphs and Line Breaks</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> tag defines a paragraph, while <code>&lt;br&gt;</code> creates a line break.</p>
    <div class="example-box">
      <p>SheCodes teaches busy women how to code.</p>
      <p>Coding workshops <br> Are available for all <br> Sign up today</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="formatting">
    <h2>Text Formatting</h2>
    <p>HTML provides various tags for text formatting:</p>
    <div class="example-box">
      <p><em>&lt;em&gt; makes text italic</em> - used for emphasis</p>
      <p><strong>&lt;strong&gt; makes text bold</strong> - used for importance</p>
      <div class="horizontal-line-demo">
        <p>Horizontal lines with <code>&lt;hr&gt;</code>:</p>
        <p>Coding workshops</p>
        <hr>
        <p>are available for all</p>
        <hr>
        <p>Sign up today</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="lists">
    <h2>HTML Lists</h2>
    <p>HTML provides ordered (<code>&lt;ol&gt;</code>) and unordered (<code>&lt;ul&gt;</code>) lists.</p>
    <div class="example-box">
      <h3>Unordered List</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>HTML</li>
        <li>CSS</li>
        <li>JavaScript</li>
        <li>C++</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Ordered List</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>HTML</li>
        <li>CSS</li>
        <li>JavaScript</li>
        <li>C++</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="links">
    <h2>Anchor Tags and Images</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> tag defines hyperlinks, and the <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tag embeds images.</p>
    <div class="example-box">
      <h3>Links Example</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.google.com">Google (same tab)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.google.com" target="_blank">Google (new tab)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.pexels.com/">Free stock images</a></li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Image Example</h3>
      <div class="image-container">
        <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/30063037/pexels-photo-30063037.jpeg" alt="Walkway through garden" width="500" height="500">
        <p>Beautiful walkway (source: Pexels)</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>More Info</h2>
    <p>SheCodes offers coding workshops for women in a supportive environment. Courses include HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and more.</p>
    <div class="example-box">
      <h3>What we offer:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Codes</strong> - Various programming languages</li>
        <li><strong>Course</strong> - Structured learning paths</li>
        <li><strong>Stories</strong> - Alumni success stories</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Join our community of women in tech today!</p>
    </div>
  </section>

